As a key source of food for other fish and a major filter for the algae and other particles in the bay the menhaden ecologically speaking is the most important animal in the bay the Chesapeake Bay Foundation says
Many of the remaining skipjacks have become museum pieces like the Martha Lewis in Baltimore preserved by the Chesapeake Heritage Conservancy and the EC Collier now in the Chesapeake Bay Maritime Museum in St Michaels
The Chesapeake Bay Foundation will file a lawsuit against the Environmental Protection Agency Wednesday signaling a more aggressive strategy for a group that has grown increasingly frustrated over the slow progress in cleaning up the bay
